    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-16T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-16T11:00:00-05:00" n="536"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2870: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-16T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 16—3:31 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1075. Your 742, July 15, noon. Foreign Office did not expect us to communicate on
                    behalf of British but to be the first Government to announce its approval which
                    British would immediately follow by announcement on its own behalf. No objection
                    whatever to our mentioning that we are aware that British Government concurs.
                    British Embassy, Tokyo, already appropriately instructed.</p>
                <pb facs="0652" n="554" xml:id="pg_554"/>
                <p>Have we communicated [to] Japan our approval of the letters? Has Japan accepted
                    formula referred to in my 1057, July 3 [<hi rend="italic">13</hi>], 7 p.m.?</p>
                <p>Paris informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
